caption: Delicate ceiling installations at Boomrock this week. We started collecting bits and pieces of dried flowers nearly two years ago for this wedding. A lot of thought and love went into these designs and we feel pretty proud of how this turned out. Our wedding work is about passion, beauty, romance and creating art with flowers and foliage.
We love ranunculas...
In love with these two tone ranunculas- quirky and pretty all at once.

A foliage bouquet for the Brides and Bubbles event at Astra Bridal last night. Most of the elements in this bouquet were from my garden so it was pretty fun to make.
Thanks so much to Lisa and her team from @astrabridal.wellington for hosting us and to Charlotte and Paula from @wgtnweddingshow for organising the event.
We love a bit of a colour clash, in a good way of course!

One of my favourite commissions lately. I had a smile on my face as I worked on this design to fill this gorgeous Iris Apfel planter from @jonesandco_  with dried flowers. 
This arrangement had to be bright, bold and happy just like the great woman herself @iris.apfel

A little birthday high tea yesterday with amazing delights created by Mahalia. My darling daughter baked for many hours to create these delights and she did an amazing job. I had such a lovely time with a beautiful group of friends. 
The Kowhai is from my garden and it’s the best it’s ever flowered. Maybe it’s the warmer weather we’ve been having this year? Everyone took home their own jar of daffodils and Kowhai to welcome Spring. 
Thanks for all the love. 
Friends, flowers, food and champagne... la vita è bella!
